---
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base title="Sandbox CLI" description="Instant ephemeral dev environments via SSH. Run sandbox ssh, get a fresh Ubuntu container, disconnect and it's gone. No cleanup, no clutter.">
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="hero-label">Sandbox CLI</p>
      <h1 class="hero-title">A fresh dev environment.<br />In one command.</h1>
      <p class="hero-subtitle">
        Run <code>sandbox ssh</code>, get a fully-loaded Ubuntu container via SSH.<br />
        When you disconnect, it disappears. No cleanup. No leftover junk.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-terminal">
        <div class="terminal-bar">
          <span class="dot red"></span>
          <span class="dot yellow"></span>
          <span class="dot green"></span>
          <span class="terminal-title">Terminal</span>
        </div>
        <pre class="terminal-body"><span class="prompt">$</span> sandbox ssh
<span class="output">Creating container... done</span>
<span class="output">Connecting via SSH...</span>
<span class="prompt">root@sandbox-7f3a:~#</span> node server.js
<span class="output">Server running on :3000</span>
<span class="comment"># disconnect when done — container auto-destroys</span></pre>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a href="#install" class="btn-primary">Install Now</a>
        <a href="https://github.com/mvtrdmqv88-droid/sandbox-cli" target="_blank" class="btn-secondary">View on GitHub</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Pain Points -->
  <section class="pain-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">Sound familiar?</h2>
      <div class="pain-grid">
        <div class="pain-card">
          <div class="pain-icon">&#128169;</div>
          <h3>"My machine is a mess"</h3>
          <p>Three versions of Node, two Pythons, a Go that you installed for a tutorial in 2024 and never touched again. Your laptop is a graveyard of dev tools.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pain-card">
          <div class="pain-icon">&#128556;</div>
          <h3>"Works on my machine"</h3>
          <p>You spent two hours debugging only to realize it was a local config issue. Again. A clean environment would have told you in 5 minutes.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pain-card">
          <div class="pain-icon">&#9200;</div>
          <h3>"Setting up takes forever"</h3>
          <p>You just want to test one thing. But first: install dependencies, configure env vars, set up the database... By the time you're ready, you've lost momentum.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- How It Works -->
  <section class="how-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">How it works</h2>
      <div class="steps-grid">
        <div class="step-card">
          <div class="step-number">1</div>
          <h3>Install</h3>
          <p>One command. Works on macOS and Linux. Docker is the only dependency.</p>
          <code class="step-code">brew install fixitdev/tap/sandbox</code>
        </div>
        <div class="step-card">
          <div class="step-number">2</div>
          <h3>Connect</h3>
          <p>Run <code>sandbox ssh</code> and you're inside a fresh Ubuntu container in seconds.</p>
          <code class="step-code">sandbox ssh</code>
        </div>
        <div class="step-card">
          <div class="step-number">3</div>
          <h3>Disconnect</h3>
          <p>Close the SSH session. The container is destroyed automatically. Zero cleanup.</p>
          <code class="step-code">exit</code>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Features -->
  <section class="features-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">What you get</h2>
      <div class="features-grid">
        <div class="feature-item">
          <h3>Instant SSH access</h3>
          <p>No port-forwarding setup, no Docker exec gymnastics. Just SSH into a real container.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-item">
          <h3>Auto-cleanup</h3>
          <p>Containers self-destruct on disconnect. Your Docker gets no chance to accumulate junk.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-item">
          <h3>Web Dashboard</h3>
          <p>See active containers, usage stats, and session history at a glance. Built with Next.js.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-item">
          <h3>SQLite-backed</h3>
          <p>All session data stored locally in SQLite. No external database. No cloud dependency.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-item">
          <h3>Configurable images</h3>
          <p>Default Ubuntu, but you can point it at any Docker image you want.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-item">
          <h3>Lightweight daemon</h3>
          <p>Written in Go. The daemon uses minimal resources and starts instantly.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Pricing -->
  <section class="pricing-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">Pricing</h2>
      <p class="pricing-intro">Start free. Upgrade if you need more.</p>
      <div class="pricing-grid">
        <div class="price-card">
          <h3>Free</h3>
          <p class="price">$0</p>
          <ul class="price-features">
            <li>3 containers per day</li>
            <li>30-minute session limit</li>
            <li>Auto-cleanup</li>
            <li>Web Dashboard</li>
            <li>Community support</li>
          </ul>
          <a href="#install" class="btn-secondary">Get Started</a>
        </div>
        <div class="price-card featured">
          <h3>Pro</h3>
          <p class="price">$4.99<span class="price-period">/month</span></p>
          <ul class="price-features">
            <li>Unlimited containers</li>
            <li>No time limit</li>
            <li>Auto-cleanup</li>
            <li>Web Dashboard</li>
            <li>Priority support</li>
            <li>Custom base images</li>
          </ul>
          <a href="#install" class="btn-primary">Start Pro</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Install -->
  <section id="install" class="install-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">Install</h2>
      <div class="install-options">
        <div class="install-option">
          <h3>Homebrew (macOS / Linux)</h3>
          <pre class="install-code">brew install fixitdev/tap/sandbox</pre>
        </div>
        <div class="install-option">
          <h3>Go install</h3>
          <pre class="install-code">go install github.com/mvtrdmqv88-droid/sandbox-cli@latest</pre>
        </div>
        <div class="install-option">
          <h3>From source</h3>
          <pre class="install-code">git clone https://github.com/mvtrdmqv88-droid/sandbox-cli.git
cd sandbox-cli && make install</pre>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="install-note">Requires Docker to be installed and running.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ -->
  <section class="faq-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">FAQ</h2>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Do I need Docker installed?</summary>
          <p>Yes. Sandbox CLI uses the Docker SDK under the hood to create and manage containers. If you have Docker Desktop or Docker Engine running, you're good to go.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>What happens to my files when I disconnect?</summary>
          <p>They're gone. That's the whole point. If you need to persist files, mount a volume with <code>sandbox ssh --volume ./myproject:/workspace</code>.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Can I use a custom Docker image?</summary>
          <p>Absolutely. Pass <code>--image your-image:tag</code> to use any image you want. The default is Ubuntu with common dev tools pre-installed.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Is this a hosted service?</summary>
          <p>Nope. Everything runs locally on your machine. Your data never leaves your laptop. The Pro license just unlocks usage limits in the CLI.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>How is this different from VS Code Dev Containers?</summary>
          <p>Dev Containers are great for long-running project environments. Sandbox CLI is for quick, throwaway sessions. Need to test something? <code>sandbox ssh</code>. Done? Close the terminal. No config files, no project setup.</p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Bottom CTA -->
  <section class="bottom-cta">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Stop polluting your machine. Start sandboxing.</h2>
      <p>One command to a fresh environment. Zero cleanup when you're done.</p>
      <a href="https://github.com/mvtrdmqv88-droid/sandbox-cli" class="btn-primary">Try Sandbox CLI Free</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  /* Hero */
  .hero {
    padding: 5rem 0 3rem;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .hero-label {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .hero-title {
    font-size: 2.75rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    line-height: 1.2;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }
  .hero-subtitle {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    max-width: 560px;
    margin: 0 auto 2.5rem;
  }
  .hero-subtitle code {
    background: var(--color-surface);
    padding: 0.15rem 0.4rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }
  .hero-actions {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    justify-content: center;
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  /* Terminal */
  .hero-terminal {
    max-width: 560px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    border-radius: 10px;
    overflow: hidden;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    text-align: left;
  }
  .terminal-bar {
    background: #1e1e1e;
    padding: 0.6rem 1rem;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.4rem;
  }
  .dot {
    width: 10px;
    height: 10px;
    border-radius: 50%;
  }
  .dot.red { background: #ff5f57; }
  .dot.yellow { background: #febc2e; }
  .dot.green { background: #28c840; }
  .terminal-title {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    margin-left: 0.5rem;
  }
  .terminal-body {
    background: #0d0d0d;
    padding: 1.25rem;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--color-text);
    overflow-x: auto;
  }
  .prompt { color: var(--color-success); }
  .output { color: var(--color-text-muted); }
  .comment { color: #555; }

  /* Buttons */
  .btn-primary {
    display: inline-block;
    background: var(--color-accent);
    color: #fff;
    padding: 0.75rem 1.75rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    font-weight: 600;
    transition: background 0.2s;
  }
  .btn-primary:hover { background: var(--color-accent-hover); text-decoration: none; }
  .btn-secondary {
    display: inline-block;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    color: var(--color-text);
    padding: 0.75rem 1.75rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    font-weight: 600;
    transition: border-color 0.2s;
  }
  .btn-secondary:hover { border-color: var(--color-text-muted); text-decoration: none; }

  /* Section basics */
  .section-title {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  /* Pain Points */
  .pain-section { padding: 4rem 0; }
  .pain-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }
  .pain-card {
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 1.5rem;
  }
  .pain-icon { font-size: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  .pain-card h3 { font-size: 1.05rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .pain-card p { color: var(--color-text-muted); font-size: 0.9rem; }

  /* How It Works */
  .how-section { padding: 4rem 0; }
  .steps-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }
  .step-card {
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 1.5rem;
  }
  .step-number {
    width: 32px;
    height: 32px;
    background: var(--color-accent);
    color: #fff;
    border-radius: 50%;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }
  .step-card h3 { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .step-card p { color: var(--color-text-muted); font-size: 0.9rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  .step-card code { color: var(--color-text-muted); font-size: 0.85rem; }
  .step-code {
    display: block;
    background: #0d0d0d;
    padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem;
    border-radius: 6px;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--color-success);
  }

  /* Features */
  .features-section { padding: 4rem 0; }
  .features-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }
  .feature-item {
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 1.5rem;
  }
  .feature-item h3 { font-size: 1rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .feature-item p { color: var(--color-text-muted); font-size: 0.9rem; }

  /* Pricing */
  .pricing-section { padding: 4rem 0; }
  .pricing-intro { color: var(--color-text-muted); margin-top: -1.5rem; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  .pricing-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.25rem;
    max-width: 650px;
  }
  .price-card {
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 2rem;
  }
  .price-card.featured { border-color: var(--color-accent); }
  .price-card h3 { font-size: 1.1rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .price {
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }
  .price-period { font-size: 0.9rem; font-weight: 400; color: var(--color-text-muted); }
  .price-features {
    list-style: none;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }
  .price-features li {
    padding: 0.35rem 0;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }
  .price-features li::before {
    content: "\2713  ";
    color: var(--color-success);
    margin-right: 0.25rem;
  }

  /* Install */
  .install-section { padding: 4rem 0; }
  .install-options {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }
  .install-option {
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 1.5rem;
  }
  .install-option h3 { font-size: 0.95rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  .install-code {
    background: #0d0d0d;
    padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
    border-radius: 6px;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--color-success);
    overflow-x: auto;
  }
  .install-note {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }

  /* FAQ */
  .faq-section { padding: 4rem 0; }
  .faq-list { max-width: 700px; }
  .faq-item {
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    padding: 1rem 0;
  }
  .faq-item summary {
    font-weight: 600;
    cursor: pointer;
    color: var(--color-text);
    font-size: 1rem;
  }
  .faq-item summary:hover { color: var(--color-accent); }
  .faq-item p {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
    padding-left: 0.25rem;
  }
  .faq-item code {
    background: var(--color-surface);
    padding: 0.1rem 0.3rem;
    border-radius: 3px;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
  }

  /* Bottom CTA */
  .bottom-cta {
    padding: 4rem 0;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .bottom-cta h2 { font-size: 2rem; font-weight: 800; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .bottom-cta p { color: var(--color-text-muted); margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .hero-title { font-size: 1.75rem; }
    .hero-subtitle { font-size: 0.95rem; }
    .hero-actions { flex-direction: column; align-items: center; }
  }
</style>
